  "prompt": "I am an animator. Should I go for a Wacom product or a Huion product?",
  "response": "Both Wacom and Huion offer quality drawing tablets, and the best choice depends on your specific needs and budget. Here's a comparison:\n\nWacom Pros:\n- Industry standard\n- Extremely reliable\n- Excellent build quality\n- Superior pen pressure sensitivity\n- Better customer support\n- More accurate pen tracking\n\nWacom Cons:\n- More expensive\n- Heavier\n- Limited budget options\n\nHuion Pros:\n- More affordable\n- Lightweight\n- Good value for money\n- Comparable features to Wacom\n- Larger working areas\n- Newer models with advanced features\n\nHuion Cons:\n- Less consistent build quality\n- Slightly lower pen pressure sensitivity\n- Less reliable customer support\n- Some users report driver/software issues\n\nRecommendations:\n- If budget is not an issue and you want professional-grade equipment, choose Wacom\n- If you're a student or budget-conscious, Huion offers excellent value\n- For professional animation work, Wacom Intuos Pro or Cintiq are top choices\n- For hobbyists or beginners, Huion Kamvas or Wacom Intuos are good options\n\nUltimately, test both if possible and choose based on your personal preference and workflow.",
